People with higher education have a higher repayment rate. 
Customers who are repeaters are finding it difficult to repay the loans
People with greater annuity have not defaulted as much as others. 
People with low income category have defaulted on loans and hence the bank can take precautions while handing out loans
The banks can trust people who are students, businessmen and pensioners to repay their loans on time. 
Owning a car is not a vindictive metric in defining a person will default or not. 
People in the married segment with an academic degree must be a cautious segment for the bank while handing out loans. 
